SIMPLE: helpless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helpless
<hw>Help"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of help or
strength; unable to help or defend one's self; needing help; feeble;
weak; <as>as, a helpless infant</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How shall I then your <qex>helpless</qex> fame defend?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Beyond help; irremediable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some <qex>helpless</qex> disagreement or dislike, either of mind
or body.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bringing no help; unaiding.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet since the gods have been⟦br⟧
<qex>Helpless</qex> foreseers of my plagues.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Unsupplied; destitute; -- with <xex>of</xex>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Helpless</qex> of all that human wants require.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Help"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Help"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helpmate</ent>⟦br⟧
